description: Latin venenatus, past participle of venenare (“to poison”), from venenum (“poison, venom”).

adjectives.description: venenate (comparative more venenate, superlative most venenate)

verbs.description: venenate (third-person singular simple present venenates, present participle venenating, simple past and past participle venenated)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To poison; to infect with poison.
examples: assume a venene nature , which expiring infecd and venenate the Air
